variables.name: mLatitudeDegrees
variables.comment:
* For documentation of below fields, see corresponding fields in {@link
         * GnssMeasurementCorrections}.

methods.name: public Builder setLatitudeDegrees(@FloatRange(from = -90.0f, to = 90.0f) double latitudeDegrees)
methods.comment: Sets the latitude in degrees at which the corrections are computed.

methods.name: public Builder setLongitudeDegrees(@FloatRange(from = -180.0f, to = 180.0f) double longitudeDegrees)
methods.comment: Sets the longitude in degrees at which the corrections are computed.

methods.name: public Builder setAltitudeMeters(@FloatRange(from = -1000.0f, to = 10000.0f) double altitudeMeters)
methods.comment:
* Sets the altitude in meters above the WGS 84 reference ellipsoid at which the corrections
         * are computed.

methods.name: public Builder setHorizontalPositionUncertaintyMeters(@FloatRange(from = 0.0f) double horizontalPositionUncertaintyMeters)
methods.comment:
* Sets the horizontal uncertainty (68% confidence) in meters on the device position at
         * which the corrections are provided.

methods.name: public Builder setVerticalPositionUncertaintyMeters(@FloatRange(from = 0.0f) double verticalPositionUncertaintyMeters)
methods.comment:
* Sets the vertical uncertainty (68% confidence) in meters on the device position at which
         * the corrections are provided.

methods.name: public Builder setToaGpsNanosecondsOfWeek(@IntRange(from = 0) long toaGpsNanosecondsOfWeek)
methods.comment: Sets the time of applicability, GPS time of week in nanoseconds.

methods.name: public Builder setSingleSatelliteCorrectionList(@NonNull List<GnssSingleSatCorrection> singleSatCorrectionList)
methods.comment:
* Sets a the list of {@link GnssSingleSatCorrection} containing measurement corrections for
         * a satellite in view

methods.name: public Builder setEnvironmentBearingDegrees(@FloatRange(from = 0.0f, to = 360.0f) float environmentBearingDegrees)
methods.comment:
* Sets the environment bearing in degrees clockwise from true north, in the direction of
         * user motion. Environment bearing is provided when it is known with high probability
         * that velocity is aligned with an environment feature (such as edge of a building, or
         * road).
         *
         * Both the bearing and uncertainty must be set for the environment bearing to be valid.

methods.name: public Builder setEnvironmentBearingUncertaintyDegrees(@FloatRange(from = 0.0f, to = 180.0f) float environmentBearingUncertaintyDegrees)
methods.comment:
* Sets the environment bearing uncertainty in degrees.
         *
         * Both the bearing and uncertainty must be set for the environment bearing to be valid.

methods.name: public GnssMeasurementCorrections build()
methods.comment: Builds a {@link GnssMeasurementCorrections} instance as specified by this builder.
